    <div class="copy col-md-pull-4 col-md-8">
      <p>In my role as the Content Architect at AEO, I played a pivotal role in orchestrating the transition from the traditional CMS (Oracle WCS) to the innovative headless CMS solution, Contentstack.</p>
      <p>After extensive consultations with design and content authoring teams, I formulated a strategy that placed the marketing message, or "lockup," at the core of the content architecture. This strategic shift laid the foundation for a more efficient and streamlined content management process.</p>
      <p>The solution I devised allowed for the creation of marketing messages in a central location, ensuring consistency across various channels and content types. By creating the message once and leveraging it in multiple areas, we established a system that facilitated effortless updates and maintained a cohesive brand message.</p>
      <p>To enhance flexibility, I abstracted visual control from the message itself. This approach enabled customization of visual elements specific to each location, ensuring that while the core message remained consistent, its appearance could be tailored for different contexts. This not only maintained brand consistency but also accommodated diverse visual requirements.</p>
      <p>As a final touch, I introduced the concept of an entry "library" that housed reusable content. This library significantly reduced bloated assets and minimized the time required to recreate redundant information. The content library became a valuable resource for efficiently managing and reusing content elements, contributing to a more streamlined and resource-efficient content management system.</p>
      <p>The implementation of these strategic initiatives not only facilitated a smooth transition to Contentstack but also revolutionized AEO's content management approach. The focus on the "lockup," visual customization, and the content library collectively contributed to enhanced efficiency, reduced redundancy, and improved consistency across all channels.</p>
      <p>My role as the Content Architect during AEO's CMS transition reflects my commitment to developing strategic solutions that optimize content management processes. This experience underscores my ability to align technology with business goals, resulting in innovative and efficient solutions that drive organizational success.</p>
